15 SECTION 1.
16 An Act establishing the State Court of Spalding County, formerly known as the City Court
17 of Griffin, approved December 14, 1897 (Ga. L. 1897, p. 462), as amended, is amended by
18 repealing all of its existing sections and provisions and replacing them as follows:
19 "SECTION 1.
20 (a) The State Court of Spalding County, originally established as the City Court of Griffin
21 by an Act approved December 14, 1897 (Ga. L. 1897, p. 462), as amended, is continued
22 in existence and shall have the power, jurisdiction, and method of procedure as provided
23 by Chapter 7 of Title 15 of the O.C.G.A.
24 (b) As used in this Act, the term 'State Court' means the State Court of Spalding County.
25 SECTION 2.
26 The State Court of Spalding County shall be located in the county site of Spalding County
27 in facilities provided by the governing authority of Spalding County.
28 SECTION 3.
29 The State Court of Spalding County shall have such rules of practice and procedure as
30 provided by Chapter 7 of Title 15 of the O.C.G.A. or by rules promulgated by the Supreme
31 Court of Georgia.
32 SECTION 4.
33 The State Court of Spalding County shall have identical terms to the Spalding County
34 Superior Court as stated in Code Section 15-6-3 of the O.C.G.A. in the county site of
35 Spalding County and such terms remain open for the transaction of business until the next
36 succeeding term. If the date fixed for the convening of any term is a legal holiday, then
37 that term shall begin on the next day thereafter which is not a legal holiday. Said court
